title: Fish fry! (Better late than never.)
summary: You can never have too many main course recipes, so give Fish fry! (Better late than never.) a try. This dairy free and pescatarian recipe serves 3 and costs $10.54 per serving. One serving contains 1284 calories, 103g of protein, and 67g of fat. This recipe from Unami Girl has 1 fans. Head to the store and pick up mayonnaise, salt and pepper, when that happened, and a few other things to make it today. To use up the frying oil you could follow this main course with the Paleo Fried Apple Pies as a dessert. All things considered, we decided this recipe deserves a spoonacular score of 80%. This score is great. Try New England Fish Fry, Stay Up Late, and A Late One Highball for similar recipes.

winePairing.pairingText: Pinot Grigio, Gruener Veltliner, and Pinot Noir are my top picks for Fish. Fish is as diverse as wine, so it's hard to pick wines that go with every fish. A crisp white wine, such as a pinot grigio or Grüner Veltliner, will suit any delicately flavored white fish. Meaty, strongly flavored fish such as salmon and tuna can even handle a light red wine, such as a pinot noir. The Prophecy Pinot Grigio with a 4 out of 5 star rating seems like a good match. It costs about 10 dollars per bottle.

productMatches.title: Prophecy Pinot Grigio
productMatches.description: The Pinot Grigio offers the best of the high altitude delle Venezie region. Flavors of light citrus, tropical fruit, and mineral notes offer crisp, refreshment and are complemented by delicate floral aromas.
